name: Palazzo Braschi
description:
Palazzo Braschi, a palace in Rome, was once covered by the face of Mussolini and dozens of printed "SI" (Italian for "yes"). It referred to the 1934 Italian general election, which was a simple yes-no vote for the Fascist Party list. This NFT is a modern take on this historical event where Mussolini face is replaced my a new fictitious despot called Gustav. 

By https://twitter.com/DonnetPA
